WEBVTT

00:41.959 --> 00:44.086
I'm gonna miss you.

00:44.127 --> 00:45.796
Wish I didn't have to go.

00:47.089 --> 00:49.383
I love you so much.

00:50.676 --> 00:53.679
Now you're gonna take your pills,
sweetheart, huh?

00:55.097 --> 00:57.891
All right? Don't just chew 'em up
and spit 'em out. [Chuckles]

00:58.892 --> 01:02.104
I can't believe you're traveling, mom.
I know how much you hate to fly.

01:02.229 --> 01:06.316
Yeah, I do, but some things are important.

01:06.400 --> 01:08.694
Thank you for letting me
leave him with you.

01:08.735 --> 01:11.697
- Of course. He's a cutie.
- [Both chuckle]

01:11.738 --> 01:13.532
Hey, kids! Come say hi to grandma!

01:13.615 --> 01:15.284
[Girl] I'm on the phone!

01:15.409 --> 01:17.828
So, um, the yellow pills are twice a day,

01:17.869 --> 01:19.538
- and the blue ones...
- I know, mom.

01:19.621 --> 01:20.998
You gave me the list, remember?

01:21.123 --> 01:22.541
Yeah, I know, but...

01:22.583 --> 01:24.710
And these are his toys.

01:24.751 --> 01:27.546
- And he sleeps with Mr. Moose.
- Hey!

01:27.588 --> 01:29.228
If you guys don't come in here right now,

01:29.256 --> 01:31.466
I'm gonna flush your phones
down the toilet!

01:31.550 --> 01:33.719
I don't wanna see them...
I mean, i-i'm...

01:33.844 --> 01:36.263
I don't wanna disturb them.
I know they're busy.

01:37.598 --> 01:39.474
And hey, don't you yell so much!

01:39.558 --> 01:41.435
I don't want you to stress him out.

01:41.560 --> 01:44.062
- Mom...
- He's already... freaked.

01:44.146 --> 01:45.480
[Footsteps approaching]

01:45.564 --> 01:47.149
I don't think he' stressed. He's fine.

01:47.190 --> 01:50.444
- Hi, grandma.
- Oh, hi, Tommy!

01:50.485 --> 01:52.362
So... who died?

01:52.446 --> 01:54.156
Oh, an old, old friend.

01:54.281 --> 01:56.950
Hey, maybe you'll play
with dashiell some time.

02:00.329 --> 02:01.747
Maybe.

02:03.206 --> 02:04.666
[Footsteps depart]

02:04.750 --> 02:06.585
Okay, um...

02:08.754 --> 02:11.298
If anything should happen,

02:11.340 --> 02:14.009
know that I love you, dashiell. Yeah.

02:14.092 --> 02:16.470
Mommy loves you
and you're gonna be taken care of.

02:16.595 --> 02:19.097
Okay, mom, stop being so dramatic.

02:19.181 --> 02:21.350
Okay? Flying is very safe.

02:21.391 --> 02:23.226
You'll be back before you know it.

02:23.352 --> 02:25.187
Nothing is gonna happen.

02:36.365 --> 02:38.367
[Birds chirping]

02:52.214 --> 02:53.799
[Indistinct chatter]

02:58.220 --> 02:59.221
[Allie] Claire!

02:59.262 --> 03:00.514
Allie.

03:00.639 --> 03:02.391
So glad you came.

03:02.516 --> 03:04.559
- Thanks for letting me know.
- Oh.

03:04.685 --> 03:07.062
Of course. Mom really missed you.

03:07.145 --> 03:08.397
She really loved you.

03:09.523 --> 03:10.816
I loved her.

03:10.941 --> 03:13.276
- Stop it! I can see you!
- [Indistinct noise]

03:13.402 --> 03:14.403
Three now.

03:14.444 --> 03:16.738
[Giggles] Three,
can you believe it? Stop it!

03:16.822 --> 03:20.534
Dad will be really glad you came.
It'll mean a lot to him.

03:20.575 --> 03:22.577
[Indistinct chatter]

03:25.122 --> 03:26.432
- Wonderful.
- [Woman chuckles]

03:26.456 --> 03:29.167
I'm wearing high heels in honor of Joyce.

03:29.292 --> 03:30.961
- Aww.
- She had such great legs,

03:31.002 --> 03:33.004
and she always loved to show them off.

03:33.088 --> 03:36.758
- She did! She had the best legs.
- [All chuckle]

03:36.842 --> 03:38.593
Claire! Oh, you made it!

03:38.719 --> 03:41.388
Oh, that would mean so much to her.

03:41.430 --> 03:44.182
This is Claire,
one of Joyce's oldest friends.

03:44.307 --> 03:46.393
They were at college together.

03:46.435 --> 03:49.396
[Raising voice] Claire lives in Ohio now.

03:49.438 --> 03:53.191
- We're so sorry for your loss.
- Oh, bless you, darling.

03:53.316 --> 03:55.026
Call us and come over to dinner, Howard.

03:55.110 --> 03:58.405
- Thank you, I will.
- [Woman] We love you.

03:59.865 --> 04:01.158
[Sighs] Claire.

04:01.283 --> 04:04.077
Howard... I'm gonna kill you.

04:05.454 --> 04:08.415
Now that she's gone,
now that it can't hurt her,

04:08.457 --> 04:09.624
I'm gonna kill you.

04:10.792 --> 04:14.629
This weekend.
I'm gonna do it this weekend.

04:15.881 --> 04:17.466
[Woman 2] Howard, oh!

04:17.591 --> 04:20.719
- Dear Howard! Oh, you dear man!
- Oh, hi. Hi, hi.

04:20.761 --> 04:23.013
I'm so, so sorry.

04:24.181 --> 04:26.641
You think you'll get used to it,

04:26.767 --> 04:29.102
used to the idea of loss.

04:30.312 --> 04:33.356
When you see it this far
over the horizon...

04:34.816 --> 04:38.361
It's like that shot
in Lawrence of Arabia,

04:38.487 --> 04:42.908
you know, the little speck
that gets closer and closer.

04:44.618 --> 04:45.952
[Light coughing]

04:49.498 --> 04:50.916
I learned a lot.

04:52.334 --> 04:54.503
I changed a lot.

04:54.544 --> 04:58.173
I learned Patience, humility.

04:58.256 --> 05:00.550
I learned...

05:00.675 --> 05:02.803
- To enjoy lattes.
- [All chuckling]

05:02.928 --> 05:08.517
Some of you know that Joyce
just loved her afternoon lattes,

05:08.558 --> 05:11.394
and she got me addicted
to them as well.

05:12.395 --> 05:16.525
Sometimes I... think
I can still hear her say...

05:16.650 --> 05:21.530
"Howie! Go to the cafe
and get some lattes, will ya?"

05:21.655 --> 05:23.031
[All laughing]

05:26.368 --> 05:27.828
[Sighs]

05:27.869 --> 05:30.163
I met Joyce in New York.

05:33.166 --> 05:34.584
We were married...

05:34.709 --> 05:37.420
[Sighs] Seven months after we'd met.

05:39.005 --> 05:43.009
And I have no regrets.

05:45.554 --> 05:47.222
None.

05:50.559 --> 05:55.188
Darling, I just want you to know,
from the bottom of my heart...

05:55.272 --> 05:57.107
Is this the wrong entrance?

05:57.190 --> 05:59.067
Said "chapel" on the door.

05:59.150 --> 06:00.694
[Howard stammers]

06:00.735 --> 06:02.988
- Oh...
- Howard.

06:03.071 --> 06:05.282
- Did I interrupt your eulogy?
- [Mourners murmuring]

06:05.407 --> 06:08.076
- God, I'm sorry.
- That's all right, Evelyn.

06:08.159 --> 06:10.453
It's all right, please.
Everyone, this is Evelyn.

06:10.579 --> 06:15.083
Um... Evelyn was Joyce's
college roommate,

06:15.166 --> 06:17.711
- believe it or not.
- Why wouldn't they believe it?

06:17.752 --> 06:19.754
- That's just an expression.
- I was in the back,

06:19.838 --> 06:21.882
using the restroom. It's like a maze.

06:21.923 --> 06:24.301
- Understood. Yeah.
- A labyrinth.

06:24.426 --> 06:27.137
Nice photo.
A bit sanitized, maybe.

06:27.220 --> 06:30.015
- What?
- Well, she looks pleasant,

06:30.098 --> 06:33.852
but Joyce was never just pleasant.
She was always sparkly.

06:33.894 --> 06:36.897
"Sparkly"? Evelyn,
would you mind taking a seat?

06:37.022 --> 06:38.022
Would you mind, please?

06:38.064 --> 06:41.484
I'm in the middle of my eulogy to my wife.

06:41.568 --> 06:44.154
My wife of 51 years has just died!

06:44.237 --> 06:47.365
I understand. My friend just died.

06:47.490 --> 06:51.328
My friend of 60 years. How 'bout that?

06:51.453 --> 06:52.662
Isn't that something?

06:52.787 --> 06:53.872
[Howard sighs]

06:55.457 --> 06:58.877
Oh, go ahead.
You were saying something about...

06:58.960 --> 07:02.464
"No regrets," "darling Joyce,"
"bottom of my heart."

07:02.505 --> 07:04.883
[Howard sighs] Yes, I...

07:04.966 --> 07:07.886
- I was about to say...
- [Groans lightly]

07:07.969 --> 07:12.515
I admired her courage
in fighting this awful disease.

07:13.475 --> 07:16.019
[Pop music playing]

07:25.820 --> 07:28.114
Evelyn! Evie!

07:29.908 --> 07:31.785
It's-it's me, it's Claire.

07:31.826 --> 07:33.536
Hi, Claire. I know it's you.

07:33.620 --> 07:35.997
I haven't lost my marbles. Yet.

07:36.081 --> 07:38.708
- Or my eyesight.
- Get in.

07:38.833 --> 07:43.088
- Let me give you a ride.
- Do you have a driver's license?

07:43.171 --> 07:46.424
- I do. I took the test two months ago.
- [Scoffs]

07:46.549 --> 07:49.177
And you passed?
Did you bribe the instructor?

07:49.260 --> 07:52.681
I didn't have to!
I'm an excellent driver.

07:52.722 --> 07:55.016
- I trust the bus more.
- Oh, get in!

07:55.100 --> 07:56.434
I need to talk to you.

07:56.559 --> 07:59.854
About what? What do you need
to talk about?

07:59.980 --> 08:01.648
- [Car honking]

08:01.731 --> 08:03.984
- [Man] Come on, move it!
- God, hold your horses!

08:04.067 --> 08:06.736
What kind of person honks a horn
in a graveyard?

08:06.820 --> 08:10.031
Jeez! Pass, there's room. Go!

08:10.115 --> 08:12.742
- You jerk!
- Get in, Evie!

08:12.867 --> 08:15.745
I... I need to talk to you.

08:15.870 --> 08:17.622
I told him.

08:17.706 --> 08:19.749
You told him what?

08:19.833 --> 08:24.004
I told him I was gonna kill him
this weekend.

08:24.045 --> 08:25.588
I'm gonna kill the bastard.

08:25.672 --> 08:27.674
- [Birds chirping]
- [Sprinklers spraying]

08:29.426 --> 08:32.595
I could chat. A little bit.

08:32.679 --> 08:34.889
- [Claire coughs]
- You're not gonna kill anyone.

08:36.016 --> 08:38.351
- I am.
- You always had big ideas,

08:38.435 --> 08:40.645
but very little follow-through.

08:40.729 --> 08:41.730
Not true!

08:41.771 --> 08:44.458
Oh, what about the time you were gonna
go out in the middle of the night

08:44.482 --> 08:47.485
and paint a vagina
on that fraternity house?

08:48.653 --> 08:50.363
I don't remember that.

08:50.447 --> 08:52.115
You talked about it for weeks,

08:52.198 --> 08:55.910
you were gonna do it for homecoming.

08:55.994 --> 08:57.412
No kidding! What happened?

08:58.496 --> 09:01.249
Nothing! Nothing happened.
You never did it.

09:03.168 --> 09:07.630
Or what about the time you were gonna
become a lounge singer?

09:07.714 --> 09:09.382
Or drive down to Peru?

09:09.466 --> 09:13.428
- There's still time.
- [Groans, laughs]

09:13.511 --> 09:17.807
- Are you still playing?
- 'Course I'm still playing!

09:17.891 --> 09:21.436
Without my cello, I'd be lost,
completely lost!

09:21.519 --> 09:24.272
- Well, good for you!
- Mm.

09:24.355 --> 09:26.399
I'm not with the orchestra anymore.

09:26.483 --> 09:28.193
I'm with a couple of ensembles.

09:28.276 --> 09:33.239
One is devoted totally
to modern composers,

09:33.323 --> 09:36.076
and the other is all bach.

09:36.159 --> 09:38.328
Do-do you still have
that cute little house?

09:38.411 --> 09:42.290
- Mm-hmm.
- Oh, that's wonderful. Wonderful.

09:43.291 --> 09:45.376
Um, so I was wondering...

09:45.460 --> 09:48.004
If-if you could help me.

09:48.088 --> 09:49.839
What, murder him?

09:49.964 --> 09:52.842
There's a little thing called jail.

09:52.967 --> 09:56.387
Nice place to visit,
but you wouldn't want to live there.

09:56.471 --> 10:00.350
And let's take a moment to remember
our beautiful, kind, happy friend

10:00.433 --> 10:02.060
whose funeral we attended today.

10:02.143 --> 10:03.853
I've thought about her.

10:03.978 --> 10:07.232
I prioritized her happiness over mine,

10:07.315 --> 10:09.567
over my-my sanity.

10:09.692 --> 10:12.737
She never asked you to do anything.

10:12.821 --> 10:15.824
And I told you,
I told you to go the police.

10:15.865 --> 10:18.993
Yeah, you did.
They wouldn't have believed me.

10:19.035 --> 10:20.203
I mean, back then?

10:22.539 --> 10:24.666
"Why were you alone in that house?

10:24.749 --> 10:27.168
You knew your friend was out of town."

10:28.253 --> 10:30.505
"Why were you alone
in your best friend's house

10:30.588 --> 10:32.132
with her husband?"

10:32.215 --> 10:35.552
Mm. "Best friend." I thought
I was your best friend at that time.

10:35.677 --> 10:38.012
You were both my best friends!

10:38.054 --> 10:40.098
I'm just yankin' your chain.

10:40.181 --> 10:43.059
It would've ruined her life
if! Had told the police.

10:44.435 --> 10:45.895
We'll never know.

10:46.020 --> 10:47.981
Her life might've been better.

10:53.945 --> 10:55.196
What's the plan?

10:55.280 --> 10:58.032
I'm gonna shoot him.
I'm gonna buy a gun

10:58.116 --> 11:00.493
and I'm gonna take it to the wake.

11:00.577 --> 11:03.163
- Mm-hmm.
- You wanna come with me?

11:05.373 --> 11:07.917
Sure, scarface. Sounds like fun.

11:10.378 --> 11:11.378
[Chuckles]

11:18.386 --> 11:19.220
Oh!

11:19.304 --> 11:20.972
- [Door closes]
- Uh, hello.

11:21.014 --> 11:23.808
- Hello.
- I-I'd like to buy a handgun.

11:23.892 --> 11:26.728
- Mm-hmm.
- Um, something not to heavy, please.

11:26.811 --> 11:29.439
- And maybe a silencer.
- Hm.

11:29.522 --> 11:31.524
Well, I can't sell you a silencer.

11:31.608 --> 11:33.860
You can't legally buy
a suppressor in California.

11:33.943 --> 11:35.403
- Tsk.
- Oh.

11:35.486 --> 11:36.905
You can wear earplugs.

11:36.988 --> 11:39.741
Well, what kind of firearm
would you recommend for me?

11:39.824 --> 11:42.285
I want something that's... light.

11:42.368 --> 11:43.912
Well, what're you gonna use it for?

11:43.995 --> 11:46.080
Tell 'im.

11:46.164 --> 11:47.957
Sport shooting? Self defense?

11:47.999 --> 11:49.167
Yea... self defense.

11:49.250 --> 11:52.420
Okay, well, how about
this little Davis derringer? [Sighs]

11:52.503 --> 11:53.671
Fits right in your pocket,

11:53.796 --> 11:55.516
or your pocketbook,
right next to your keys.

11:55.590 --> 11:57.842
- Oh, it's cute!
- Very!

11:57.926 --> 12:01.471
.22 caliber, two shots.
Nice backup piece.

12:01.554 --> 12:03.056
- [Gun clicks]
- Wanna hold it?

12:03.139 --> 12:06.643
- Oh, sure!
- It's used, costs about $125.

12:06.768 --> 12:08.853
- It's light!
- How's the recoil?

12:08.937 --> 12:10.939
- [Seller clears throat]
- Recoil?

12:10.980 --> 12:14.359
Um, not gonna lie, it has a little kick.
Not much there to absorb the shock.

12:14.442 --> 12:15.526
[Gun clicking]

12:15.610 --> 12:17.987
Do you have arthritis
in your wrists and hands?

12:18.071 --> 12:20.782
A little bit in my-in my left wrist.

12:20.865 --> 12:23.618
But I take medication.
Hips are my problem.

12:23.701 --> 12:25.536
Mine too! I got
a hip replacement last year.

12:25.620 --> 12:27.330
Oh, how'd that go for you?

12:27.413 --> 12:30.959
Pretty good, thanks.
I also recommend this beretta 92.

12:31.000 --> 12:32.543
[Gun clicking]

12:33.544 --> 12:34.671
Looks heavier.

12:34.796 --> 12:37.799
It has very little recoil.
Very smooth, feels like a Cadillac.

12:37.882 --> 12:39.050
[Chamber clicks]

12:39.133 --> 12:41.970
I think that the key here is
to use a load that lessens the kick.

12:43.221 --> 12:45.682
These .9mm bullets are very lightweight.

12:46.849 --> 12:49.185
Hollow point for maximum damage.

12:49.269 --> 12:51.187
Oh, maximum damage sounds neat.

12:51.271 --> 12:53.273
Yeah, I'll take... I'll take
the smaller gun.

12:53.356 --> 12:57.193
Um, okay. I'll need your California
driver'slicense or your Cal ID,

12:57.277 --> 13:00.113
and you can take the handgun safety test
right here in the store.

13:00.196 --> 13:02.490
I don't have a California license.

13:02.573 --> 13:05.201
- You don't have California license?
- No, I live in Ohio.

13:05.285 --> 13:09.163
[Scoffs] Then I can't
sell you a gun. Sorry.

13:10.999 --> 13:12.625
Well, darn it! We tried.

13:12.709 --> 13:13.751
[Door opens]

13:18.006 --> 13:20.174
So, did you get that out of your system?

13:21.676 --> 13:24.387
The whole dirty Harry,
death wishthing?

13:24.470 --> 13:27.098
No, I didn't get it out of my system!

13:27.181 --> 13:29.559
- God!
- [Distant siren wailing]

13:29.642 --> 13:31.936
I should've bought
a gun at home and brought it.

13:32.020 --> 13:36.149
[Scoffs] Couldn't have gotten it
on the plane.

13:36.274 --> 13:39.986
Oh, Claire, it's been decades,
and not like a couple of decades,

13:40.028 --> 13:43.031
it's been four and a half decades!

13:43.114 --> 13:46.034
[Emotional] It was yesterday.

13:46.117 --> 13:47.702
Yeah.

13:47.785 --> 13:49.412
Oh, I remember.

13:49.495 --> 13:52.623
The necklace Joyce was wearing
in the photo, at the funeral home?

13:52.707 --> 13:54.459
I gave her that necklace.

13:54.542 --> 13:57.003
- I had one too.
- Do you have any poison?

13:58.087 --> 14:01.966
I have a cyanide pill in case I'm captured
by the enemy. You can have it.

14:02.008 --> 14:04.802
I'm just gonna have to stab him
in the stomach.

14:04.927 --> 14:06.763
- [Laughs]
- Are you going to the wake?

14:06.888 --> 14:10.350
No. I'll read about it
in the newspaper tomorrow.

14:10.433 --> 14:12.727
I have a rehearsal.

14:12.810 --> 14:14.020
You hate him too!

14:14.103 --> 14:17.357
I don't hate anybody, it's too exhausting.

14:17.440 --> 14:21.027
Well, let me give you
a-a ride to your house.

14:21.110 --> 14:23.946
I think I'd rather take the bus.

14:24.030 --> 14:26.991
Evie... Evie...

14:27.033 --> 14:28.201
[Scoffs]

14:31.496 --> 14:34.123
You're the only person I ever told.

14:34.207 --> 14:36.334
Jesus! Really?

14:40.338 --> 14:42.673
Well... except for a therapist.

14:44.384 --> 14:47.678
I had a therapist
after my second divorce.

14:47.762 --> 14:50.390
Clearly it's done wonders for you.

14:50.473 --> 14:53.393
Evie... come with me.

14:53.476 --> 14:55.770
Bye, Claire.

15:03.361 --> 15:06.364
["Your shadow"
by Sharon Van etten playing]

15:28.761 --> 15:30.138
Hey, Ernie.

15:30.221 --> 15:33.224
["Your shadow" continues]

15:36.144 --> 15:37.562
How's it hanging, Phil?

15:42.400 --> 15:43.401
[Keys jingling]

16:00.334 --> 16:01.419
[Sighs]

16:13.723 --> 16:15.641
[Tuning notes]

16:19.437 --> 16:22.440
[Playing classical tune]

16:34.911 --> 16:35.828
[Groans]

16:35.912 --> 16:37.622
Oh, god...

16:41.334 --> 16:43.336
[Groaning] Oh, god...

16:43.461 --> 16:45.463
Oh, goddammit!

16:49.509 --> 16:50.635
[Knocks on door]

16:51.928 --> 16:53.638
[Knocking]

16:53.679 --> 16:55.556
Yes?

16:55.640 --> 16:57.350
- [Bow clatters]
- [Knocking resumes]

16:57.475 --> 17:00.478
Yes. [Grunts] Coming!

17:03.648 --> 17:05.816
- Hi!
- Remember me?

17:05.942 --> 17:07.818
'Course I remember you!

17:07.944 --> 17:10.071
Are you visiting your grandpa again?

17:10.196 --> 17:12.073
My parents are over there.

17:12.114 --> 17:14.075
- Mm.
- I wanted to come and say hi.

17:14.200 --> 17:18.204
- Well, thanks!
- Can I come in?

17:18.246 --> 17:21.123
Oh, sure, for a second.

17:25.002 --> 17:26.963
Aren't your parents gonna miss you?

17:27.088 --> 17:30.132
- [Door latches]
- They didn't miss me last time.

17:31.133 --> 17:32.969
That day we played checkers.

17:34.095 --> 17:36.097
- [Sighs] Wanna play again?

17:37.723 --> 17:38.975
You know, um...

17:39.976 --> 17:42.520
I can't right now.

17:42.603 --> 17:45.815
Um... how's your grandfather? How's Walt?

17:47.108 --> 17:50.403
He wants to teach me how to throw a ball
and shoot a gun.

17:51.988 --> 17:53.239
Oh, does he have one?

17:53.281 --> 17:54.991
He has a baseball.

17:55.116 --> 17:58.411
But does he have a, uh, gun?

17:58.536 --> 17:59.536
Yeah.

18:00.413 --> 18:03.249
- He has a gun. [Chuckles]
- I think so.

18:03.291 --> 18:06.544
He showed it to me.
He says he wants to teach me.

18:07.545 --> 18:08.545
Huh.

18:09.714 --> 18:12.008
Can we do that other thing
we did last time?

18:13.301 --> 18:14.427
The fashion show?

18:15.428 --> 18:18.723
Well, you did look cool in those heels.

18:18.848 --> 18:21.309
[Sighs] But I don't have time right now.

18:22.560 --> 18:25.563
- Oh...
- Wait, wait. Come here, come here.

18:27.148 --> 18:31.444
Tell you what, you can choose
something from this to keep.

18:32.445 --> 18:35.072
- Really?
- Why not?

18:35.156 --> 18:38.451
Who else am I gonna leave 'em to?

18:38.492 --> 18:40.369
Oh, except you can't have this one...

18:40.453 --> 18:43.873
Or this one, and this one I got in Seoul

18:43.956 --> 18:46.959
when I traveled all over
with the orchestra.

18:49.629 --> 18:50.796
Can I have this?

18:50.880 --> 18:52.798
Your ears aren't pierced, are they?

18:52.882 --> 18:54.508
- Tsk.

18:54.634 --> 18:57.511
Mm... not those, but how about these?

18:57.637 --> 18:59.764
These are clip-ons.

18:59.805 --> 19:02.683
See, you open them like that,
and you clip them...

19:03.893 --> 19:05.936
Pop 'em right onto your earlobes.

19:06.020 --> 19:09.482
- They don't pinch, do they?
- No, it's fine.

19:09.523 --> 19:11.025
Well, go look at yourself.

19:16.030 --> 19:17.698
Wow!

19:17.782 --> 19:20.201
They're... beautiful.

19:20.326 --> 19:21.494
[Light chuckle]

19:21.619 --> 19:23.788
You're beautiful, kid.

19:27.249 --> 19:29.251
[Gasps, sighs]

19:31.504 --> 19:32.546
[Smooches]

19:34.382 --> 19:36.926
- Better get back to your parents.
- ' [9'99'931

19:44.433 --> 19:45.976
Hey... hey!

19:49.438 --> 19:50.398
[Mouths] Bye.

19:50.439 --> 19:51.941
[Door opens]

19:53.275 --> 19:54.568
[Door closes]

20:07.665 --> 20:09.375
Oh, Joyce...

20:09.417 --> 20:10.960
[Sighs]

20:11.001 --> 20:13.963
[Exhales sharply]
Oh, to hell with all this!

20:14.004 --> 20:15.464
[Closes jewelry box]

20:18.384 --> 20:20.010
[Indistinct chatter]

20:24.765 --> 20:26.308
[Kid screaming]

20:31.439 --> 20:33.107
May I take your coat?

20:39.739 --> 20:41.031
[Howard] Yes.

20:42.616 --> 20:43.617
Where's the kitchen?

20:43.743 --> 20:46.454
- The kitchen or the bathroom?
- Kitchen.

20:46.495 --> 20:49.874
Right in there. It's pretty busy
in there right now.

20:49.915 --> 20:51.333
Good.

20:51.459 --> 20:53.061
- [Caterer] What are you doing over here?
- Oh!

20:53.085 --> 20:54.712
- Looking for the bathroom?
- No.

20:54.754 --> 20:56.481
[Caterer] That's not the right order.
I want...

20:56.505 --> 20:59.091
Tomato, olive, cheese.
Tomato, olive, cheese.

21:00.926 --> 21:03.637
- Can I help you, ma'am?
- No, thanks.

21:03.721 --> 21:04.865
No, wait! What are you doing?

21:04.889 --> 21:06.769
Those go back in there
for another five minutes.

21:06.891 --> 21:09.185
[Knives swishing]

21:09.310 --> 21:11.312
[Caterer continues talking, indistinct]

21:14.231 --> 21:15.608
I love chocolate. I just can't.

21:15.649 --> 21:17.943
Oh, wait! Is that for me? Thanks.

21:17.985 --> 21:20.112
Claire, have you ever met Wendy?

21:20.196 --> 21:23.616
Wendy brought us
this beautiful batch of brownies.

21:23.657 --> 21:26.619
- Isn't that wonderful?
- [Wendy] The least I can do.

21:26.660 --> 21:28.954
- Your mom was so wonderful.
- Thank you.

21:28.996 --> 21:31.499
I was her art teacher. She was
a very talented painter.

21:31.624 --> 21:34.543
- Was she?
- Oh, yes!

21:34.668 --> 21:37.838
Thank you. Would you do me a favor
and run that back to the kitchen?

21:37.963 --> 21:40.549
Guys! No more sugar.

21:40.674 --> 21:43.260
- No, you're gonna go crazy.
- [Wendy laughs]

21:53.813 --> 21:54.939
[Breathing heavily]

22:10.996 --> 22:12.957
[Ralph, distorted] Claire?

22:12.998 --> 22:14.166
Claire?

22:15.167 --> 22:16.418
It's me, Ralph.

22:16.502 --> 22:17.502
[Shocked sigh]

22:19.380 --> 22:21.966
Ralph! What are you doing here?

22:22.007 --> 22:26.136
Oh, Howard just called me out of the blue
and invited me to the memorial.

22:26.220 --> 22:27.972
I wasn't busy, so I came.

22:29.265 --> 22:31.183
Well... when did he call you?

22:31.267 --> 22:34.979
Afew hours ago. I hope
you don't mind that I'm here.

22:35.020 --> 22:37.565
I was very fond of Joyce.

22:37.606 --> 22:39.108
You two were great friends.

22:39.191 --> 22:42.736
And he told me that you were here.

22:44.530 --> 22:47.074
- You look nice, Ralph.
- Thank you.

22:47.157 --> 22:48.534
I'm glad you're still alive.

22:48.617 --> 22:51.161
[Disbelieving chuckle] Me too!

22:51.245 --> 22:53.747
[Light chuckle] It's good to see you.

22:55.416 --> 22:57.751
Why-why are you carrying that knife?

22:58.752 --> 23:01.255
Oh, I was gonna stab someone.

23:01.338 --> 23:03.465
- [Laughing] Come on!
- [Chuckles]

23:04.466 --> 23:06.093
Crab cakes?

23:07.177 --> 23:10.222
Uh, would you take this
to the kitchen for me? Thank you.

23:10.306 --> 23:13.267
Uh, is that a no on the crab cakes?

23:13.350 --> 23:15.769
That's a no, yes, thank you.

23:17.438 --> 23:18.230
[Glasses clink]

23:18.314 --> 23:22.026
So... how are you? How's your husband?

23:23.986 --> 23:27.323
[Smacks lips]
We were divorced 15 years ago.

23:27.448 --> 23:29.617
Oh, I'm-I'm sorry.

23:29.658 --> 23:31.785
How's your wife?

23:31.911 --> 23:34.455
Uh, she passed about four years ago.

23:34.496 --> 23:38.459
- Oh, I'm sorry.
- But she lived a good, full life,

23:38.500 --> 23:40.586
and I loved her deeply.

23:40.669 --> 23:42.880
- Well, that's good.
- [Chuckles]

23:42.963 --> 23:45.674
I had no idea why I said that.

23:45.799 --> 23:48.969
I mean, it just goes without saying.
I guess...

23:50.471 --> 23:53.682
- Guess I'm a little nervous.
- Why?

23:53.807 --> 23:56.602
Well, it isn't very often that you...

23:56.685 --> 23:59.521
Not very often that you run
into your ex-wife?

23:59.647 --> 24:01.357
Not very often.

24:03.484 --> 24:04.818
[Smacks lips] Any kids?

24:04.944 --> 24:08.948
I have one kid, two grandkids.

24:08.989 --> 24:11.283
- Great-grands?
- They're not that great.

24:11.367 --> 24:13.160
[Laughing]

24:13.243 --> 24:15.245
No, I have no great-grandkids.

24:15.329 --> 24:16.914
- I have a corgi.
- Mm!

24:16.997 --> 24:18.999
- Pictures?
- Of course!

24:19.083 --> 24:20.518
- How could I not, right?
- Of course!

24:20.542 --> 24:22.836
- It's what we do these days.
- [Chuckling]

24:24.296 --> 24:25.631
Let me see...

24:26.632 --> 24:28.550
[Claire on video] Come on, dashiell.
Come on!

24:28.634 --> 24:30.010
- [Chuckles]
- Give me a smile.

24:31.387 --> 24:34.014
- Oh, good boy!
- Cute, huh?

24:34.098 --> 24:36.934
Oh, dogs always loved you, Claire.

24:37.017 --> 24:38.060
Yeah. You?

24:39.979 --> 24:43.607
- Oh... lovely!
- [Chuckling]

24:43.691 --> 24:45.234
Lovely!

24:45.317 --> 24:46.986
[Ralph] Ahem.

24:51.699 --> 24:53.409
It's really nice to see you.

24:56.537 --> 25:00.416
- I hope I didn't scare you.
- Oh, come on!

25:00.541 --> 25:02.042
You're as beautiful as ever.

25:02.126 --> 25:05.045
[Chuckles] And you're as kind as ever.

25:05.129 --> 25:07.715
Look at you two lovebirds!

25:07.756 --> 25:10.134
Or "love pterodactyls," maybe.

25:10.217 --> 25:12.261
[Chuckling] Evelyn.

25:12.344 --> 25:15.139
- Hi, Ralph.
- You came!

25:15.222 --> 25:17.099
I didn't miss the carnage, did I?

25:17.182 --> 25:18.851
[Distant indistinct chatter]

25:20.561 --> 25:23.647
I think someone
is about to give a speech.

25:23.731 --> 25:26.734
Oh, good. Perfect timing.

25:29.570 --> 25:31.739
[Allie] I know my mother...

25:32.698 --> 25:37.244
My mother would be... so happy
to see you all here.

25:37.327 --> 25:41.248
She'd really appreciate,
I know dad and I do.

25:42.583 --> 25:44.918
So please eat, drink,

25:45.002 --> 25:48.005
and raise a toast to my mom.

25:49.006 --> 25:50.507
The best mom in the world.

25:50.632 --> 25:52.885
[All] To Joyce!

25:52.968 --> 25:53.969
[Howard] Yes.

25:58.307 --> 26:02.269
- Um, I have a few words to say.
- Please.

26:02.352 --> 26:05.689
Uh, this is Evelyn,
one of my mother's oldest friends.

26:07.649 --> 26:10.069
Joyce was a wonderful woman.

26:10.152 --> 26:12.237
- [Kids chattering]
- She certainly was.

26:12.321 --> 26:13.989
[Evelyn] A great cook.

26:14.031 --> 26:16.075
A devoted wife and mother.

26:16.158 --> 26:18.035
A doting grandmother.

26:18.118 --> 26:19.411
[Murmurs of appreciation]

26:19.495 --> 26:22.456
And forjunior
and senior years in college,

26:22.539 --> 26:27.002
and then six months in New York City
after graduation,

26:27.086 --> 26:29.671
she was my roommate and my lover.

26:29.755 --> 26:30.964
[Mourners gasp]

26:31.006 --> 26:33.509
Jesus, what?

26:33.634 --> 26:36.970
And this wasn't
a "gay until graduation" type of thing.

26:37.012 --> 26:39.014
This was who she was.

26:40.432 --> 26:42.684
But not who she wanted to be.

26:43.936 --> 26:47.022
[Howard laughs, wheezily]

26:47.106 --> 26:49.233
God! [Laughing]

26:49.316 --> 26:51.193
I'm sorry, Howard. What's so funny?

26:51.276 --> 26:56.198
You are, Evelyn. You always had
such a great sense of humor.

26:56.281 --> 26:58.075
Mm, not really.

26:58.158 --> 27:02.871
People think I'm being funny,
but I'm really just talking.

27:02.996 --> 27:05.749
It's very inappropriate,
Evelyn, and untrue.

27:05.833 --> 27:08.293
And not something my children
needed to hear.

27:08.377 --> 27:10.003
Oh, was it?

27:10.087 --> 27:12.589
Did you even understand
what I was saying, honey?

27:12.714 --> 27:14.341
You said you loved grandma.

27:14.424 --> 27:18.011
[Gasps] That's right!
That's exactly what I said.

27:19.012 --> 27:21.431
Adorable grandkids.

27:21.515 --> 27:23.767
She got that in the transaction, I guess.

27:23.851 --> 27:25.894
[Howard] She told me.

27:25.978 --> 27:28.438
She told me that you were delusional,

27:28.522 --> 27:31.525
that you were infatuated with her.

27:31.608 --> 27:34.319
I mean, we used to laugh about it.

27:35.487 --> 27:38.991
She thought you were funny.
I can tell you that.

27:39.032 --> 27:41.076
She told me you were cruel.

27:41.160 --> 27:44.788
My father is one
of the kindest people I know.

27:44.872 --> 27:47.291
Oh, is he?

27:47.374 --> 27:49.084
[Allie] I think you should leave now.

27:49.168 --> 27:52.004
I tend to agree.

27:52.087 --> 27:55.465
Howard, you didn't deserve her.

27:58.760 --> 28:02.347
Um, can anyone give me a ride?

28:07.019 --> 28:10.480
So? What did you think of my big news?

28:11.857 --> 28:12.858
I knew.

28:12.941 --> 28:16.445
Two of you were always staring
at each other,

28:16.528 --> 28:18.155
mooning over each other.

28:19.531 --> 28:20.949
So why didn't you say something?

28:20.991 --> 28:23.368
Why didn't you?

28:23.452 --> 28:25.454
Joyce didn't want to.

28:27.748 --> 28:30.125
Guess I didn't either at the time.

28:31.543 --> 28:34.171
- It was a different time.
- No.

28:34.254 --> 28:37.925
You have always underestimated me.

28:38.008 --> 28:41.011
Here, pull over. Here, at the bus stop.

28:42.763 --> 28:45.933
What gives? I can drive you home.

28:46.016 --> 28:48.018
What're you afraid of?

28:58.779 --> 29:00.364
[Announcement over pa indistinct]

29:01.365 --> 29:02.532
[Evelyn] Hey.

29:10.999 --> 29:12.626
Ta-da!

29:14.378 --> 29:15.378
[Evelyn sighs]

29:17.172 --> 29:20.092
Why... why did you lie to me?

29:20.175 --> 29:22.594
Why-why did you say
you still had your house?

29:22.678 --> 29:25.847
Well, if you thought I still had my house,

29:25.931 --> 29:29.017
then for a moment there
it was as if I still had my house.

29:30.060 --> 29:32.062
Yeah, makes sense.

29:32.104 --> 29:33.522
Not really.

29:34.898 --> 29:36.984
It just got too much to keep up.

29:37.025 --> 29:40.904
I-I spent a fortune on plumbing,
the roof...

29:42.239 --> 29:44.116
I didn't have the money anymore.

29:44.199 --> 29:46.910
- I love these chairs!
- Aren't they good?

29:46.994 --> 29:50.580
But didn't you get a great pension
from the orchestra?

29:50.664 --> 29:53.917
Well, I have a modest pension.

29:54.001 --> 29:56.044
Enough to pay for this place.

29:56.128 --> 29:58.338
I'm in the independent living section,

29:58.422 --> 30:01.550
- so I come and go as I want.
- Right.

30:01.633 --> 30:04.845
For rehearsals and concerts and...

30:04.928 --> 30:07.514
Oh, yeah. [Chuckles]

30:10.600 --> 30:11.768
Sorry.

30:11.893 --> 30:14.980
Arthritis, tendonitis, bursitis.

30:15.981 --> 30:17.983
My ankles are in good shape, though.

30:19.192 --> 30:21.445
I still teach, from time to time.

30:21.528 --> 30:24.281
I do a master class, occasionally.

30:25.282 --> 30:27.284
One of my old students
teaches nearby,

30:27.326 --> 30:31.288
she has me come in,
critique the sawing.

30:32.289 --> 30:35.000
- Oh.
- She throws me a few bucks.

30:36.543 --> 30:38.503
And the meals are included here.

30:38.587 --> 30:41.965
I like eating cardboard,
so it's worked out for me.

30:42.007 --> 30:44.676
- [Chuckles]
- I can invite a guest.

30:44.760 --> 30:46.970
Wanna come to dinner?

30:47.012 --> 30:50.182
Well, you-you make it sound
so appetizing...

30:51.892 --> 30:54.144
Uh, no, but Ralph invited me to diner.

30:55.228 --> 30:56.772
Damn, you work fast!

30:56.897 --> 30:57.897
[Light chuckle]

30:59.691 --> 31:00.942
Look!

31:01.943 --> 31:04.071
Look at us!

31:04.154 --> 31:05.155
[Claire gasps]

31:08.325 --> 31:10.535
Look at us...

31:17.918 --> 31:19.836
- [Crickets chirping]
- [Distant barking]

31:31.264 --> 31:32.349
[Exhales]

31:40.816 --> 31:43.819
[Soft music playing on stereo]

31:47.114 --> 31:49.157
You were married to grandpa?

31:49.241 --> 31:50.992
Yes, I was.

31:54.287 --> 31:55.872
It's not polite to stare.

31:55.997 --> 31:59.376
- Well, you can't blame him.
- [Chuckles] That's true.

31:59.459 --> 32:01.503
- I'd stare.
- [Joie chuckles]

32:01.586 --> 32:04.089
This was before grammy?

32:04.131 --> 32:05.882
Of course it was before grammy,
knucklehead.

32:06.007 --> 32:08.802
- What do you think?
- Don't call him names. Say you're sorry.

32:09.886 --> 32:10.762
Sorry.

32:10.846 --> 32:12.681
Now tell him something nice about him.

32:12.722 --> 32:14.683
[Sighs] You're good at roblox.

32:14.766 --> 32:16.766
Now you tell your brother
something nice about him.

32:17.519 --> 32:18.520
You smell funny.

32:18.603 --> 32:20.105
[Claire and Ralph laughing]

32:20.188 --> 32:22.399
That wasn't nice. Do another one.

32:22.482 --> 32:25.402
- Uh... you're fast.
- [Ralph] Yes, he is.

32:25.444 --> 32:27.446
- I am fast.
- Very fast.

32:32.993 --> 32:37.289
It was a long, long time ago
when your grandfather and I were together.

32:37.330 --> 32:39.458
[Chuckling] Prehistoric times.

32:39.541 --> 32:41.126
- [Claire laughs]
- [Grandkid 2] Okay.

32:41.209 --> 32:43.295
How long are you in town for?

32:43.420 --> 32:47.132
Just for the weekend, the funeral.

32:48.633 --> 32:50.302
This is so good!

32:50.427 --> 32:51.803
- You're a good cook, Ralph.
- Mm.

32:51.887 --> 32:53.889
Well, I remembered you were pescatarian.

32:55.182 --> 32:56.433
Still am!

32:56.475 --> 32:57.309
[Both chuckle]

32:57.434 --> 32:58.634
[Grandkid 1] Can I be excused?

32:58.727 --> 33:01.730
- Me too, I'm full.
- What about dessert?

33:01.813 --> 33:04.024
Can I take an ice cream sandwich upstairs?

33:04.065 --> 33:05.233
You finish that salmon.

33:05.317 --> 33:07.486
I can't, I'm full.

33:07.611 --> 33:10.238
Okay, well, the garbage can
will finish it.

33:10.322 --> 33:12.324
- That's me.
- [Chuckling] Oh!

33:12.449 --> 33:14.910
I eat anything they leave.

33:15.035 --> 33:16.620
[Claire] Oh...

33:16.661 --> 33:18.955
[Joie] If you both take
your plates into the kitchen,

33:19.039 --> 33:21.833
wash them off and then put them
in the dishwasher...

33:22.834 --> 33:25.086
Then you can take
an ice cream sandwich upstairs.

33:25.170 --> 33:27.090
- [Ralph] There you go.
- [Grandkid 2] Thank you.

33:27.172 --> 33:28.548
- [Ralph] Mm-hmm.
- [Chair drags]

33:32.052 --> 33:35.055
- Good kids.
- Thank you.

33:35.096 --> 33:36.848
They are a pain in the butt.

33:36.932 --> 33:38.225
[Chuckles]

33:38.350 --> 33:40.769
It's nice that your father
has you here with him.

33:40.810 --> 33:42.938
- It certainly is.
- Yeah!

33:42.979 --> 33:45.482
Well, it's good for us,
because he's such a good cook.

33:45.565 --> 33:47.651
Yeah. [Chuckles]

33:50.862 --> 33:52.572
I think I'm gonna excuse myself as well.

33:52.656 --> 33:55.700
- It was very nice to meet you, Claire.
- You too, joie.

34:04.709 --> 34:07.295
Um... care to have an after dinner drink?

34:08.380 --> 34:09.589
Okay.

34:14.219 --> 34:16.012
Claire, there's, uh...

34:16.096 --> 34:19.808
There's something
I've always wanted to ask.

34:19.849 --> 34:20.976
Oh, god...

34:22.143 --> 34:23.395
What happened?

34:24.813 --> 34:26.106
Now, don't get me wrong.

34:26.231 --> 34:28.567
This is the best thing
that could've happened to me,

34:28.692 --> 34:30.569
I-I moved on with my life.

34:31.987 --> 34:34.406
[Scoffs] I met zora,

34:34.531 --> 34:36.533
I have kids, I have grandkids...

34:38.618 --> 34:40.870
[Sighs] But I've always wondered.

34:40.996 --> 34:43.915
Heh. So I'm gonna have
to sing for my supper, huh?

34:43.999 --> 34:46.001
- [Chuckling]
- Oh, no, no, no.

34:46.126 --> 34:49.462
You don't have to unless
you would like to.

34:52.465 --> 34:54.426
[Ralph sighs]

34:55.594 --> 34:57.721
You know, it would be nice
after all this time

34:57.846 --> 35:00.181
to have one less mystery in my life.

35:01.850 --> 35:03.310
Did you meet someone?

35:04.561 --> 35:06.146
- Meet someone?
- A man.

35:06.187 --> 35:07.747
Did you fall in love with someone else?

35:07.856 --> 35:10.150
No, no.

35:10.191 --> 35:12.319
Well, that's a relief.

35:12.444 --> 35:14.070
- [Claire chuckles]
- I guess.

35:15.739 --> 35:17.282
I mean, I thought maybe...

35:17.324 --> 35:19.284
If-if I was to be honest,

35:19.326 --> 35:21.911
I thought perhaps it was the old story.

35:21.995 --> 35:23.288
What old story?

35:23.330 --> 35:25.665
That I'm black and you're white.

35:26.791 --> 35:30.170
[Laughs] And what,
and I just suddenly realized that?

35:30.295 --> 35:33.381
[Chuckles] Maybe your father got to you.

35:35.050 --> 35:36.760
- Oh, Ralph!
- [Glass taps table]

35:38.887 --> 35:40.347
I loved you.

35:42.974 --> 35:45.477
I loved you, Ralph.

35:52.359 --> 35:53.485
And then?

35:57.906 --> 35:59.616
Something happened.

35:59.658 --> 36:01.660
- Something happened?
- Yeah.

36:01.785 --> 36:03.119
- Something bad?
- Yeah.

36:07.207 --> 36:10.960
- And you couldn't tell me?
- [Emotional] I couldn't.

36:11.044 --> 36:13.797
I couldn't, I couldn't.

36:13.838 --> 36:15.965
It made me mute.

36:16.007 --> 36:18.927
I made me... deaf. It made me...

36:19.928 --> 36:24.808
It made me blind to you
and to everything good in my life.

36:30.021 --> 36:31.439
[Sniffs]

36:32.565 --> 36:34.526
I just... couldn't.

36:34.651 --> 36:35.819
[Sniffing]

36:37.404 --> 36:39.864
Claire, Claire, Claire, i-i...

36:42.701 --> 36:45.829
- I don't understand this.
- [Quietly] I know.

36:45.954 --> 36:47.288
[Sighs]

36:52.168 --> 36:53.878
But I'm sorry.

36:59.467 --> 37:02.887
I'm sorry. I'm sorry I hurt you, Ralph.

37:12.772 --> 37:14.107
[Sighs]

37:57.192 --> 37:58.234
[Grunts]

37:59.819 --> 38:01.112
Not funny.

38:10.121 --> 38:11.331
Walter.

38:12.373 --> 38:13.917
- [Click]
- Walter.

38:13.958 --> 38:15.543
- [Groaning]
- Walt!

38:15.668 --> 38:17.003
What? Who is it?

38:17.086 --> 38:19.756
- It's Evelyn.
- You're not the nurse.

38:19.798 --> 38:22.759
No, I'm Evelyn, from the lunch room.

38:22.801 --> 38:24.344
- Oh...
- Don't get up.

38:24.385 --> 38:27.555
- [Chuckling] I couldn't if I tried to.
- Oh...

38:27.680 --> 38:29.808
What are you doing
at this time of the night?

38:29.933 --> 38:32.560
Do you have a gun? Do you?

38:32.685 --> 38:35.104
You're not allowed to have a gun in here.

38:35.188 --> 38:37.690
I imagine not, but do you?

38:37.774 --> 38:40.568
- Who told you I have a gun?
- Your grandkid.

38:40.693 --> 38:42.403
My grandson?

38:42.487 --> 38:44.823
Well, maybe, time will tell,
but let's not get into that.

38:44.948 --> 38:46.491
Where is your gun?

38:46.533 --> 38:49.118
- You leave my gun alone.
- {Gasps}

38:49.202 --> 38:51.788
- here, in this closet?
- Don't open that closet.

38:51.830 --> 38:53.414
If you do, I'm calling the nurse.

38:53.540 --> 38:56.543
Okay, all right, all right.
Just relax, Walt.

38:57.544 --> 39:03.550
Please, I would like
to borrow your gun, Walter.

39:03.591 --> 39:05.009
What for?

39:05.051 --> 39:07.804
Well, there... there's these thugs.

39:07.846 --> 39:09.848
They're threatening my friend.

39:09.889 --> 39:12.225
She lives in a rough neighborhood.

39:12.308 --> 39:14.686
But if I show them this gun,

39:14.727 --> 39:17.605
just kind of waved it around
and said, "hey!

39:17.730 --> 39:22.110
You leave my friend alone,
you misogynist creep!"

39:23.111 --> 39:24.612
Then they'd leave her alone.

39:24.696 --> 39:27.740
- That sounds harebrained.
- I suppose,

39:27.866 --> 39:30.451
but it's the god's honest truth.

39:30.577 --> 39:32.745
Will you do this for me, Walter?

39:32.871 --> 39:35.999
Will you be a hero and loan me your gun?

39:37.333 --> 39:40.628
Okay... if you do something for me.

39:40.712 --> 39:44.549
Anything! Well, almost anything.

39:44.632 --> 39:45.842
I want...

39:46.843 --> 39:49.012
[Inhales deeply] Bacon.

39:50.096 --> 39:52.557
Bacon? Okay.

39:52.640 --> 39:54.434
Should I bring you some
from the cafeteria?

39:54.475 --> 39:56.644
No, no, no, no, no,
their bacon is horrible!

39:56.769 --> 39:58.980
It's a Turkey bacon.
No, I don't like it.

39:59.063 --> 40:01.774
- I want real bacon!
- Ah...

40:01.858 --> 40:05.153
I want crispy bacon, four pieces. Oof!

40:05.236 --> 40:07.047
- [Growling playfully]
- If you do that for me,

40:07.071 --> 40:09.324
I'll give you what you want.

40:09.449 --> 40:13.286
Seems fair. I'm gonna go.
But Walter...

40:13.369 --> 40:14.954
- [Clicks]
- [Bed whirring]

40:15.038 --> 40:16.497
This was not a dream.

40:16.581 --> 40:19.500
Well, I hope not. I want that bacon!

40:19.584 --> 40:22.128
- Good night.
- [Walter groans]

40:23.838 --> 40:25.256
[Soft music playing on stereo]

40:25.340 --> 40:26.466
[Ralph] Claire?

40:28.593 --> 40:32.513
I remember when you were
saving up to buy this.

40:32.597 --> 40:35.934
- Ralph!
- [Chuckles]

40:35.975 --> 40:37.602
Oh, my god!

40:37.685 --> 40:40.521
I wrote you about it, but you said
you didn't want it anymore.

40:41.940 --> 40:43.608
All of that time studying,

40:43.691 --> 40:45.526
all those hours in the dark room...

40:45.652 --> 40:46.653
Yeah...

40:48.112 --> 40:50.657
I saved it just in case.

40:51.658 --> 40:53.117
But, then again...

40:53.201 --> 40:55.370
Packed up a bunch of old stuff.

40:57.121 --> 41:00.208
[Breathy chuckle] I wanted to be
dorothea lange.

41:00.291 --> 41:01.291
[Ralph chuckles]

41:02.543 --> 41:04.545
Oh, Ralph... [chuckles]

41:04.671 --> 41:06.339
[Sighs]

41:10.718 --> 41:12.804
It's, um... it's getting late.

41:12.845 --> 41:14.430
- I should go.
- Don't.

41:15.848 --> 41:17.058
What?

41:17.141 --> 41:18.309
Dontgo.

41:20.103 --> 41:22.855
Please. Stay.

41:26.859 --> 41:28.027
Okay.

41:31.656 --> 41:32.657
[Switch clicks]

41:33.741 --> 41:35.535
Oh, Ralph!

41:36.703 --> 41:38.538
What if-what if joie catches us?

41:38.621 --> 41:39.998
[Ralph chuckles]

41:40.039 --> 41:41.874
Claire, this is my house.

41:41.958 --> 41:44.210
I can have someone in my room if! Like.

41:44.293 --> 41:45.378
Right.

41:52.218 --> 41:53.761
May I kiss you?

41:56.055 --> 41:57.765
Why not?

42:14.657 --> 42:15.658
[Claire moans]

42:16.659 --> 42:18.619
- Oh, Ralph...
- Oh.

42:18.703 --> 42:21.414
- Gotta catch my breath.
- [Both chuckling]

42:21.497 --> 42:25.001
I'm sorry. It's, uh, it's...

42:25.084 --> 42:27.045
It's been a while.

42:27.128 --> 42:29.589
I appreciate the enthusiasm.

42:29.672 --> 42:31.716
- [Chuckles]
- [Moans lightly]

42:31.799 --> 42:33.301
One sec.

42:35.219 --> 42:36.512
[Exhales]

42:38.639 --> 42:39.515
[Uncapping bottle]

42:39.640 --> 42:41.517
Viagra?

42:41.642 --> 42:44.103
[Laughs] No, no, no.

42:44.187 --> 42:46.230
It's just my statin.

42:46.314 --> 42:49.317
I take it every night after dinner,
so I won't forget.

42:52.612 --> 42:53.696
[Sets down glass]

42:56.365 --> 42:57.492
Where were we?

42:57.617 --> 42:59.744
You brought me to your room,

42:59.827 --> 43:02.330
and you were putting
the moves on me.

43:02.413 --> 43:04.248
[Ralph chuckles]

43:10.838 --> 43:13.007
Are you fucking serious?

43:41.327 --> 43:42.703
[Chuckles]

43:45.790 --> 43:50.378
Well, if we're gonna do whatever it is
we're thinking of doing, um...

43:51.379 --> 43:53.756
I'm gonna want to ask you
to turn the lights off,

43:53.840 --> 43:57.718
but first I want to plant myself...

43:58.719 --> 44:01.848
Firmly and safely in the bed.

44:01.889 --> 44:03.099
[Both chuckling]

44:03.182 --> 44:04.976
Okay.

44:05.017 --> 44:07.770
I'm on board. Lights out.

44:11.399 --> 44:12.900
[Gasps] Ralph!

44:12.984 --> 44:15.528
Do you have a condom?
I don't wanna get knocked up.

44:15.611 --> 44:18.614
[Both laughing]

44:19.699 --> 44:21.075
[Birds chirping]

44:56.194 --> 44:58.112
[Cell phone ringing]

45:00.990 --> 45:01.991
Hello?

45:02.033 --> 45:03.618
I'm in.

45:03.743 --> 45:04.911
You're in what?

45:04.994 --> 45:07.997
- I'm in on the Howard thing.
- You are?

45:08.039 --> 45:10.750
Well, my other murder
canceled this week,

45:10.833 --> 45:13.002
so I've got time.

45:13.044 --> 45:15.379
Are you still in
or do you have second thoughts?

45:15.463 --> 45:18.758
- Which way is the wind blowing?
- I-I have not had second thoughts.

45:18.841 --> 45:20.927
[Laughing] But what difference
does it make?

45:21.010 --> 45:23.054
Here's the difference it makes.

45:23.137 --> 45:24.513
I have a gun.

45:24.597 --> 45:27.183
Or I will, as soon as I get some bacon.

45:27.266 --> 45:28.601
Some bacon?

45:28.684 --> 45:30.645
You think you can get a hold of some bacon?

45:30.770 --> 45:34.565
Well, yeah, I... I think
I can get a hold of some bacon.

45:34.649 --> 45:38.694
It's gotta be real bacon. Not veggie
bacon, not-not Turkey bacon.

45:38.819 --> 45:41.989
Old fashioned bacon,
four slices, cooked. Get it?

45:42.073 --> 45:44.116
Meet me here.

45:45.868 --> 45:47.119
Ah!

45:54.919 --> 45:56.295
[Sizzling]

45:59.799 --> 46:01.175
[Joie] Good morning.

46:01.259 --> 46:03.135
Hi! Good morning.

46:03.219 --> 46:04.595
I hope I didn't wake you up.

46:04.679 --> 46:06.472
- Oh, I smelled the bacon.
- Sorry.

46:06.555 --> 46:10.017
For what? He's a grown man.

46:11.477 --> 46:12.895
Right.

46:13.980 --> 46:15.398
You cooking us breakfast?

46:15.481 --> 46:17.650
I smelled bacon.

46:17.733 --> 46:19.819
Why don't you go back to bed?
It's very early.

46:19.902 --> 46:21.570
You can have bacon later.

46:21.654 --> 46:22.655
Okay.

46:24.448 --> 46:26.325
Are you going to be
our new grandmother?

46:26.409 --> 46:28.869
[Laughs] No. No, I'm not.

46:28.953 --> 46:30.997
Okay. That's good.

46:31.080 --> 46:33.833
Just 'cause, you know,
our old grammy.

46:33.916 --> 46:36.711
I know, yeah. I bet she was wonderful.

46:39.880 --> 46:44.427
- You're a big fan of bacon?
- Oh, big fan!

46:44.510 --> 46:46.345
Can't start my day without it.

46:47.346 --> 46:48.723
Thought you were a pescatarian.

46:48.848 --> 46:50.474
Yeah, yeah.

46:50.558 --> 46:52.476
Except after sex?

46:52.560 --> 46:54.186
[Chuckles]

46:54.270 --> 46:55.771
Funny.

46:56.897 --> 47:00.109
[Laughs] Uh, do you have a-a ziploc bag?

47:31.015 --> 47:32.683
- You got the stuff?
- Yeah.

47:32.767 --> 47:35.978
- Crispy?
- Pretty crispy. Uh...

47:36.062 --> 47:39.148
You didn't mention how crispy
it was supposed to be.

47:39.231 --> 47:42.234
I'm just curious. Follow me.

47:44.737 --> 47:47.656
- Walt. Walt!
- Mm?

47:47.740 --> 47:50.076
[Chuckling] Oh, I'm not dreaming!

47:50.159 --> 47:53.120
I told you it wasn't a dream.
This is my friend Claire.

47:53.204 --> 47:54.538
Hello, Claire.

47:54.622 --> 47:58.626
Now I'm dreaming
two beautiful ladies in my room.

47:58.709 --> 48:00.336
Well, it's very kind of you. Thank you.

48:00.378 --> 48:03.005
Oh, god, you brought it. I can smell it.

48:03.047 --> 48:05.549
- I told you.
- Can I see it?

48:05.633 --> 48:08.052
Bring it-bring it here, please.

48:08.135 --> 48:10.721
- Please!
- Oh, well, where's your thing?

48:10.805 --> 48:13.057
- [Whispers] The firearm.
- [Whispers] Oh!

48:13.140 --> 48:15.184
It's in the closet,
on the top shelf to the right.

48:15.267 --> 48:17.019
It's in a wooden box for checkers.

48:17.061 --> 48:18.729
- Checkers. All right.
- Checkers. Yes!

48:18.813 --> 48:21.482
- Um, you can have the bacon.
- [Bag rustling]

48:21.565 --> 48:23.442
- Thank you. Oh!
- J' ta-da j'

48:23.526 --> 48:24.985
thank you.

48:26.195 --> 48:29.115
Oh, my god, this is so wonderful!

48:31.200 --> 48:32.868
- Mm!
- It's not too crispy?

48:32.993 --> 48:35.579
- Uh-uh. Perfect!
- Oh, good.

48:35.663 --> 48:38.666
- [Evelyn] What isn't here?
- God, you're an angel.

48:38.749 --> 48:40.069
- [Claire sighs]
- [Walt chuckles]

48:41.001 --> 48:42.878
Hey, what did you mean when you said

48:43.003 --> 48:44.797
"time will tell" about my grandson?

48:44.880 --> 48:47.758
There's something wrong with that boy.

48:47.842 --> 48:52.179
No, nothing is wrong with James.
You're a lucky bastard.

48:52.263 --> 48:55.850
I can see the checkers,
but I can't reach them.

48:55.975 --> 48:57.101
[Knocking]

48:57.184 --> 48:59.603
- Hi, Walt.
- [Walt] Hello there.

48:59.687 --> 49:01.397
Oh, hi...

49:01.439 --> 49:03.399
This is Claire and Evelyn, my friends.

49:03.441 --> 49:06.694
- I've met Evelyn.
- Yeah, we've seen each other around.

49:06.735 --> 49:09.697
- Oh...
- Ooh, what's that you're eating?

49:09.738 --> 49:11.323
Oh, it's bacon. It's delicious!

49:11.407 --> 49:13.742
- Not supposed to eat that, Walt.
- Oh, come on.

49:13.826 --> 49:17.204
Ladies, I'm going to need
to catheterize Mr. Mangopyan,

49:17.288 --> 49:19.832
so I do believe the visit is over.

49:21.417 --> 49:23.502
Hector, would you do me a favor?

49:23.586 --> 49:25.880
There's a box up there, a checkers box.

49:26.005 --> 49:30.176
- Can you reach it?
- Sure!

49:30.301 --> 49:33.053
These ladies, they wanna borrow it.

49:33.137 --> 49:35.055
Oh, it's heavy!

49:35.139 --> 49:37.475
- What's in here?
- Oh, a gun.

49:37.558 --> 49:40.311
- [Walter laughs]
- You crack me up, Walt.

49:40.436 --> 49:42.813
- There you go.
- Oh, thank you.

49:42.897 --> 49:45.024
Happy catheter.

49:45.149 --> 49:46.525
- Thank you.
- See you soon!

49:46.609 --> 49:48.152
See you.

49:48.235 --> 49:50.154
Walt... uh-uh.

49:57.870 --> 49:59.747
[Light grunting]

50:01.624 --> 50:02.750
[Laughs]

50:02.791 --> 50:05.169
Uh, what is it? Is it a toy?

50:05.252 --> 50:08.672
It's a flare gun. I used to have
a flare gun on my sailboat.

50:10.341 --> 50:11.467
You had a sailboat?

50:11.509 --> 50:14.053
Yes, Anette and I had a sailboat.

50:14.178 --> 50:17.640
- Who's Anette?
- The woman I was married to.

50:19.183 --> 50:21.060
Oh! Well.

50:21.185 --> 50:24.772
- Good!
- I'm glad you approve.

50:24.813 --> 50:27.942
We met in 2006, married in 2009...

50:28.984 --> 50:31.237
Right before she died.

50:31.362 --> 50:34.657
She wanted to get married.
I did it for her.

50:36.200 --> 50:39.078
2009? Wow, I'm sorry.

50:40.371 --> 50:43.791
I'm sorry she died.
I'm sorry I didn't meet her.

50:44.833 --> 50:47.086
That's her, in the photograph.

50:49.964 --> 50:51.382
[Sighs]

50:52.383 --> 50:55.511
She was an amazing violinist.

50:55.594 --> 50:56.679
Not just violin.

50:56.720 --> 51:00.808
Mandolin, guitar,
any stringed instrument, she could play.

51:00.891 --> 51:04.520
- Oh, she's beautiful.
- Claire.

51:04.603 --> 51:07.106
I want to show you how this gun is loaded.

51:07.231 --> 51:08.023
[Gun clicks]

51:08.107 --> 51:10.526
You open it, press this button...

51:12.820 --> 51:15.406
This is the cartridge. Red side in.

51:17.533 --> 51:20.619
Shut it. It's loaded.

51:22.121 --> 51:24.248
But, um...

51:24.290 --> 51:26.750
You-you couldn't kill
anybody with that, could you?

51:26.834 --> 51:29.837
Oh, yes! Mostly yourself,
if you're not careful.

51:30.838 --> 51:34.633
You could burn a hole right through
someone with that.

51:34.717 --> 51:35.926
Wow.

51:36.927 --> 51:38.137
[Gun clatters]

51:38.262 --> 51:40.139
What made you decide to help me?

51:41.557 --> 51:43.601
"Since I cannot prove a lover,

51:43.726 --> 51:46.145
I am determined to prove a villain."

51:46.270 --> 51:47.646
Excuse me?

51:47.730 --> 51:50.149
Richard III, Shakespeare.

51:50.190 --> 51:51.442
[Chuckles]

51:52.610 --> 51:54.153
Only you, Evelyn.

51:55.613 --> 51:56.905
I've missed you.

51:56.989 --> 52:00.784
- You had my number.
- Well, you had my number.

52:02.328 --> 52:05.289
So we're both lousy friends.

52:05.331 --> 52:06.749
[Cell phone ringing]

52:08.334 --> 52:09.793
Who is it?

52:09.877 --> 52:11.211
It's Ralph.

52:11.337 --> 52:13.213
[Whispering] I slept with him last night.

52:13.339 --> 52:15.174
No kidding.

52:15.299 --> 52:16.383
[Ringing stops]

52:16.467 --> 52:18.177
Oh, that good, huh?

52:18.218 --> 52:20.012
No, it was-it was good, I...

52:20.095 --> 52:21.347
Just not...

52:22.473 --> 52:24.058
What I came here for.

52:28.479 --> 52:30.314
- [Line ringing]
- It's ringing.

52:32.691 --> 52:33.525
[Call connects]

52:33.651 --> 52:36.362
Yeah, ho-Howard? It's Claire.

52:36.487 --> 52:38.530
- Hello, Claire.
- [Distant children playing]

52:38.656 --> 52:41.116
- I wanna come over and see you.
- You do?

52:41.200 --> 52:43.118
- Yes.
- [Whispering] Tell him you feel bad.

52:43.202 --> 52:46.830
Yeah, I, um... I feel bad, you know?

52:46.955 --> 52:49.833
Howard, I want to come over
and apologize in person.

52:50.834 --> 52:53.921
Apologize for what?
Threatening to kill me?

52:53.962 --> 52:57.800
Uh, yeah. For that.

52:57.925 --> 53:00.969
All right, well, apology accepted.

53:01.011 --> 53:03.222
I just... I feel...

53:06.392 --> 53:08.560
Crazy, I've been just crazy, Howard.

53:08.686 --> 53:10.020
[Mouthing] Woman... woman...

53:10.104 --> 53:11.855
A crazy woman, you know, I...

53:11.980 --> 53:14.042
- [Whispering] Stress! Stress!
- It must be the stress.

53:14.066 --> 53:16.068
I've been under a lot of stress.

53:16.151 --> 53:18.404
You know, because of the traveling?

53:18.445 --> 53:20.739
- [Screams]
- Oh, Jesus! Wow!

53:20.823 --> 53:21.699
[Mutters]

53:21.740 --> 53:24.743
[Whispering] I wanna make friends.
I wanna make friends.

53:24.827 --> 53:27.037
- I hate to...
- [Evelyn whispering]

53:27.121 --> 53:30.749
I hate... I hate to think
that I came all this way...

53:32.376 --> 53:35.170
And-and to have that be the last...

53:35.295 --> 53:37.756
Time that-that, you know,
that I saw you.

53:37.840 --> 53:40.718
And so I think
I should come over and apologize

53:40.843 --> 53:43.429
before I go home. And...

53:43.554 --> 53:47.558
Somehow I feel that Joyce
wouldn't want it to end like this.

53:49.017 --> 53:52.396
[Groans] Well, look, I'm going to the park
with Allie and the kids.

53:52.438 --> 53:55.858
I... I suppose you could meet us there.

53:55.899 --> 53:58.193
Perfect. Uh, where?

54:00.279 --> 54:03.198
[Carrousel music playing]

54:18.005 --> 54:19.798
Should-should I load the gun now?

54:19.882 --> 54:24.470
I wouldn't. You don't want it
going off in your bag by accident.

54:24.595 --> 54:29.099
So, what? I just take it out and load it
right there, in front of him?

54:29.183 --> 54:31.018
[Scoffs] I guess.

54:33.353 --> 54:36.356
Look, you don't have to prove
anything to me.

54:36.482 --> 54:38.192
I already know you're ioca.

54:38.317 --> 54:40.986
No, you were right.

54:41.069 --> 54:42.446
I... oh, my god!

54:42.488 --> 54:47.034
There are so may things that I have not
ever followed through on.

54:47.117 --> 54:50.037
My dad used to call me "I.L."

54:51.038 --> 54:53.123
Short for "little loser."

54:53.207 --> 54:56.251
- [Dry chuckle]
- How crummy.

54:56.376 --> 55:00.088
I remember him,
in his uniform, at graduation.

